  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AHP RDC Ebola Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ebola Community Engagement and Prevention (ECEP) will expand on existing EVD response projects currently being implemented by CAN DO partners. It is informed by the national EVD emergency response strategy (SRP4) and will focus on: strengthening community engagement in 7 health zones (e.g. through training of health workers, leaders and groups); awareness raising through mass communication (e.g. including those with access to the general population); and EVD prevention through WASH activities (e.g. supply of hand washing kits in schools/churches/mosques) in 7 health zones reaching nearly 1.8M people in the target areas. The project will continue to build on a mass communication and WASH programming based on careful assessment of communities&#x2019; knowledge, practices and behaviours, that is tested and developed in cooperation with the communities.</narrative>
  </description>
